{"title_page": "The Side Two Tour", "text_new": "{{Primary sources|date=July 2015}}\n{{Infobox concert tour\n| concert_tour_name = The Side Two Tour\n| album = ''[[This Delicate Thing We've Made]]''\n| start_date = 3 February 2008\n| end_date = 24 February 2008\n| artist = [[Darren Hayes]]\n| number_of_legs = 1\n| number_of_shows = 9 in the United Kingdom<br/>1 in the Netherlands\n| last_tour = ''[[The Time Machine World Tour]]''<br>(2007)\n| this_tour = '''''The Side Two Tour'''''<br>(2008)\n| next_tour = ''The Secret Tour''<br>(2011)}}\n\n'''The Side Two Tour''' was the fifth concert tour undertaken by [[Australian]] singer-songwriter [[Darren Hayes]]. The shows were conceived as special concerts in which Hayes set out to perform in a more intimate setting than that of his previous [[The Time Machine World Tour|Time Machine Tour]]. The setlist was mainly made up of songs that had rarely been heard live before. 10 shows were announced \u2013 nine dates within the United Kingdom and one special show in the Netherlands.\n\nBand members: Keyboards \u2013 Justin Shave, guitars & vocals \u2013 Steve Young, drums (Netherlands) \u2013 Mark Weston\n\n==Set list==\n{{hidden\n| headercss = background: #ccccff; font-size: 100%; width: 65%;\n| contentcss = text-align: left; font-size: 100%; width: 75%;\n| header = United Kingdom<ref>{{cite web |title=DARREN HAYES SIDE TWO TOUR \u2013 A TREAT FOR THE HARDCORE FANS |url=https://eqmusicblog.com/darren-hayes-si/# |website=EQmusicblog |accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n| content = \n# \"Hero\"\n# \"Bombs Up in My Face\"\n# \"Sense of Humour\"\n# \"A Conversation With God\"\n# \"Random Blinking Light\" <small>(Acoustic Version)</small>\n# \"A Hundred Challenging Things a Boy Can Do\" <small>(Acoustic Version)</small>\n# \"Gunning Down Romance\"\n# \"Setting Sun\"\n# \"Maybe\"\n# \"Mine\" <small>(Acoustic Version)</small>\n# \"Dirty\"\n# \"Casey\"\n# \"Sing to Me\"\n# \"I Don't Care\"\n# \"So Beautiful\" <small>(The Beautiful Mix)</small>\n}}\n{{hidden\n| headercss = background: #ccccff; font-size: 100%; width: 65%;\n| contentcss = text-align: left; font-size: 100%; width: 75%;\n| header = Netherlands Show\n| content = \n# \"Hero\"\n# \"Carry On Amadeus\"\n# \"Insatiable\"\n# \"The Best Thing\"\n# \"Darkness\"\n# \"Step Into the Light\"\n# \"Mine\"\n# \"Gunning Down Romance\"\n# \"Dirty\"\n# \"Casey\"\n# \"I Want You\"\n# \"On the Verge of Something Wonderful\"\n# \"Sing to Me\"\n# \"Unlovable\"\n# \"Truly Madly Deeply\"\n# \"Affirmation\"\n# \"So Beautiful\" \n}}\n\n==Tour dates==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! width=\"150\"| Date\n! width=\"150\"| City\n! width=\"150\"| Country\n! width=\"250\"| Venue\n|- bgcolor=\"#DDDDDD\"\n| colspan=4| '''Europe'''\n|-\n|3 February 2008\n|rowspan=\"2\"|London\n|rowspan=\"8\"|United Kingdom\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[O2 Academy Islington|Academy Islington]] \n|-\n|4 February 2008\n|-\n|6 February 2008<ref name=\"Manchester The Studio events february march 2008\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ents24.com/manchester-events/life-cafe-and-the-studio-formerly-the-late-room |title=Life Cafe & The Studio (Formerly The Late Room), Manchester}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Manchester]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Studio\n|-\n|7 February 2008<ref name=\"Manchester The Studio events february march 2008\"/>\n|-\n|11 February 2008\n|[[Bristol]]\n|[[The Thekla]]\n|-\n|15 February 2008\n|[[Brighton]]\n|Barfly\n|-\n|17 February 2008\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Birmingham]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[O2 Academy Birmingham|Bar Academy]]\n|-\n|18 February 2008\n|-\n|21 February 2008\n|[[Amsterdam]]\n|Netherlands\n|[[Marcanti]] \n|-\n|24 February 2008\n|London\n|United Kingdom\n|Academy Islington\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Darren Hayes}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Side Two Tour}}\n[[Category:Darren Hayes concert tours]]\n[[Category:2008 concert tours]]\n", "text_old": "{{Primary sources|date=July 2015}}\n{{Infobox concert tour\n| concert_tour_name = The Side Two Tour\n| album = ''[[This Delicate Thing We've Made]]''\n| start_date = 3 February 2008\n| end_date = 24 February 2008\n| artist = [[Darren Hayes]]\n| number_of_legs = 1\n| number_of_shows = 9 in the United Kingdom<br/>1 in the Netherlands\n| last_tour = ''[[The Time Machine World Tour]]''<br>(2007)\n| this_tour = '''''The Side Two Tour'''''<br>(2008)\n| next_tour = ''The Secret Tour''<br>(2011)}}\n\n'''The Side Two Tour''' was the fifth concert tour undertaken by [[Australian]] singer-songwriter [[Darren Hayes]]. The shows were conceived as special concerts in which Hayes set out to perform in a more intimate setting than that of his previous [[The Time Machine World Tour|Time Machine Tour]]. The setlist was mainly made up of songs that had rarely been heard live before. 10 shows were announced \u2013 nine dates within the United Kingdom and one special show in the Netherlands.\n\nBand members: Keyboards \u2013 Justin Shave, guitars & vocals \u2013 Steve Young, drums (Netherlands) \u2013 Mark Weston\n\n==Set list==\n{{hidden\n| headercss = background: #ccccff; font-size: 100%; width: 65%;\n| contentcss = text-align: left; font-size: 100%; width: 75%;\n| header = United Kingdom<ref>{{cite web |title=DARREN HAYES SIDE TWO TOUR \u2013 A TREAT FOR THE HARDCORE FANS |url=https://eqmusicblog.com/darren-hayes-si/# |website=EQmusicblog |accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n| content = \n# \"Hero\"\n# \"Bombs Up in My Face\"\n# \"Sense of Humour\"\n# \"A Conversation With God\"\n# \"Random Blinking Light\" <small>(Acoustic Version)</small>\n# \"A Hundred Challenging Things a Boy Can Do\" <small>(Acoustic Version)</small>\n# \"Gunning Down Romance\"\n# \"Setting Sun\"\n# \"Maybe\"\n# \"Mine\" <small>(Acoustic Version)</small>\n# \"Dirty\"\n# \"Casey\"\n# \"Sing to Me\"\n# \"I Don't Care\"\n# \"So Beautiful\" <small>(The Beautiful Mix)</small>\n}}\n{{hidden\n| headercss = background: #ccccff; font-size: 100%; width: 65%;\n| contentcss = text-align: left; font-size: 100%; width: 75%;\n| header = Netherlands Show\n| c