{"title_page": "Young K", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=February 2020}}\n{{Korean name|Kang}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name            = Young K\n| image           = 2017 Young K Taiwan.jpg\n| image_size      = \n| caption         = Young k at Day6 Live & Meet in Taiwan, July 21, 2017\n| native_name     = \uac15\uc601\ud604\n| birth_name      = Kang Young-hyun\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1993|12|19}} \n| birth_place     = South Korea\n| alma_mater      = [[Dongguk University]]\n| occupation      = {{hlist|Musician|singer|songwriter|rapper}}\n| module          = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[Rock music|Rock]]}}\n| instrument      = {{hlist|Vocals|bass guitar}}\n| years_active    = 2015\u2013present\n| label           = [[JYP Entertainment|JYP]]\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[Day6]]|[[JYP Nation]]}}\n|module       = {{Infobox Korean name |child=yes\n|title       = [[Korean name]]\n|hangul      = {{linktext|\uac15|\uc601|\ud604}}\n|hanja       = {{linktext|\u59dc|\u6c38|\u665b}}\n|rr          = Kang Yeong-hyeon\n|mr          = Gang Y\u014fnghy\u014fn\n|hangulstage = {{linktext|\uc601}}\ucf00\uc774\n|hanjastage  = \n|rrstage     = Yeong K\n|mrstage     = Y\u014fng K\n}}}}}}\n\n'''Kang Young-hyun''' (born December 19, 1993),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&query=Young%20K&sm=ppl_cts&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService&os=2934542|title=Young K :: \ub124\uc774\ubc84 \uc778\ubb3c\uac80\uc0c9|website=people.search.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2017-10-01}}</ref> known professionally as '''Young K''', is a South Korean musician, singer, songwriter and rapper. He is best known as the bassist, vocalist and rapper of South Korean rock band [[Day6]].\n\n== Early life ==\nYounghyun was born on December 19, 1993, in [[South Korea]]. He moved to [[Toronto|Toronto, Canada]], to attend middle and high school at [[York Mills Collegiate Institute]]. He went by his English name, Brian Kang, during that time. On October 5, 2017, he received his bachelor's degree in Business Administration from [[Dongguk University]]. He graduated from University on August 23, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201808232137542410|title=\ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4 \uc601\ucf00\uc774, \uc624\ub298(23\uc77c) \ub3d9\uad6d\ub300 \uacbd\uc601\ud559\uacfc \uc878\uc5c5 \u2018\ud559\uc0ac\ubaa8 \uc778\uc99d\uc0f7\u2019|last=Lee|first=Min-ji|date=August 23, 2018|work=Newsen|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nDuring his time in high school, Kang pursued music in a three-member band called \"3rd Degree\". They performed at various locations in Toronto and put up videos on YouTube (including some original songs composed by Kang).\n\nIn 2010, Kang and his bandmate, Don Lee, were contacted by [[JYP Entertainment]] for an audition and was accepted as trainees. Lee later left JYP to pursue medical studies. Kang went on to appear in the fourth episode of ''WIN: Who is Next?''<ref>{{Cite web|title = Preview of YG vs JYP trainees on 'WIN' revealed {{!}} allkpop.com|url = http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/09/preview-of-yg-vs-jyp-trainees-on-win-revealed|website = www.allkpop.com|access-date = 2016-01-25}}</ref> as a part of JYP's rapping team with [[Got7]]'s Mark Tuan and [[Jackson Wang]] against the combined rapping teams of [[Winner (band)|Team A]] and [[iKon (South Korean band)|Team B]], where he became known for the verse, \"[[YG Entertainment|YG]], get an attitude!\" He was also a part of JYP's vocalist team alongside his eventual [[Day6]] bandmates Junhyeok, [[Jae Park|Jae]], Sungjin and Wonpil.\n\nIn 2014, Kang was selected as a member of five-member rock band 5Live under JYP, but their debut was cancelled. The band was reformed as Day6 after the addition of drummer Dowoon in 2015.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\nKang has been credited with much of the songwriting in Day6's discography. In 2019, he composed and contributed lyrics to a track for the solo debut of [[B.A.P (South Korean band)|B.A.P]]'s Youngjae entitled \"Hope\". He has also been featured as rapper in various JYP label mates' singles, such as [[Baek A-yeon]] and [[Park Ji-min (singer, born 1997)|Park Ji-min]].{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Day6 discography}}\n\n=== Songs ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Year\n!Peak chart position\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Sales<br><small>([[Music download|DL]])</small>\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Album\n|-\n![[Gaon Digital Chart|KOR]]<br><ref>Charted songs:\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=26&hitYear=2015&termGbn=week|title=Shouldn't Have}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?pageNo=2&serviceGbn=ALL&termGbn=week&hitYear=2016&targetTime=35&nationGbn=K|title=Young\ud574}}\n</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" |As featured artist\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Shouldn't Have\" <small>([[Baek A-yeon]] feat. Young K)</small>\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2015\n|1\n|\n* KOR: 2,500,000+<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/article/p.view.gaon?idx=14409|title=Gaon's \uad00\ucc30\ub178\ud2b8|trans-title=Gaon's Observation Notes|publisher=[[Gaon Music Chart]]|first=Daniel|last=C.|date=September 12, 2018|accessdate=September 12, 2018}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\" {{N/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Sky High\" <small>([[Park Sae-byul]] & Likes, Likes feat. Young K)</small>\n|\u2014\n|{{N/a}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Young\ud574\" <small>([[Park Ji-min (singer, born 1997)|Park Ji-min]] feat. Young K)</small>\n|2016\n|157\n|\n* KOR: 13,829<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=S1020&targetTime=35&hitYear=2016&termGbn=week|title=2016\ub144 35\uc8fc\ucc28 Download Chart (see #97)|publisher=Gaon Music Chart|language=ko}}</ref>\n|''[[19 to 20]]''\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" |<small>\"\u2014\" denotes that the song did not chart in the region.</small>\n|}\n\n== Filmography==\n\n===Television series===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Dream High]]'' ||Jason backup dancer  || [[KBS2]] || Cameo, episode 3\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Dream High 2]]'' ||I:dn backup dancer  || [[KBS2]] || Cameo, episode 1\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Web series ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-  \n! Year\n! Title\n! Network\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" | 2016 \n| ''Touching You''\n| [[Naver|Naver TV Cast]] \n| \n| Cameo, episode 11\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Day6}}\n{{JYP Entertainment}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Young K}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:JYP Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:South Korean bass guitarists]]\n[[Category:South Korean male idols]]\n[[Category:South Korean male rappers]]\n[[Category:South Korean male singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean pop rock singers]]\n[[Category:Day6 members]]\n[[Category:Male bass guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century bass guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century male musicians]]\n[[Category:King of Mask Singer contestants]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=February 2020}}\n{{Korean name|Kang}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name            = Young K\n| image           = 2017 Young K Taiwan.jpg\n| image_size      = \n| caption         = Young k at Day6 Live & Meet in Taiwan, July 21, 2017\n| native_name     = \uac15\uc601\ud604\n| birth_name      = Kang Young-hyun\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1993|12|19}} \n| birth_place     = South Korea\n| alma_mater      = [[Dongguk University]]\n| occupation      = {{hlist|Musician|singer|songwriter|rapper}}\n| module          = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[Rock music|Rock]]}}\n| instrument      = {{hlist|Vocals|bass guitar}}\n| years_active    = 2015\u2013present\n| label           = [[JYP Entertainment|JYP]]\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[Day6]]|[[JYP Nation]]}}\n|module       = {{Infobox Korean name |child=yes\n|title       = [[Korean name]]\n|hangul      = {{linktext|\uac15|\uc601|\ud604}}\n|hanja       = {{linktext|\u59dc|\u6c38|\u665b}}\n|rr          = Kang Yeong-hyeon\n|mr          = Gang Y\u014fnghy\u014fn\n|hangulstage = {{linktext|\uc601}}\ucf00\uc774\n|hanjastage  = \n|rrstage     = Yeong K\n|mrstage     = Y\u014fng K\n}}}}}}\n\n'''Kang Young-hyun''' (born December 19, 1993),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&query=Young%20K&sm=ppl_cts&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService&os=2934542|title=Young K :: \ub124\uc774\ubc84 \uc778\ubb3c\uac80\uc0c9|website=people.search.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2017-10-01}}</ref> known professionally as '''Young K''', is a South Korean musician, singer, songwriter and rapper. He is best known as the bassist, vocalist and rapper of South Korean rock band [[Day6]].\n\n== Early life ==\nKang was born on December 19, 1993, in [[South Korea]]. He moved to [[Toronto|Toronto, Canada]], to attend middle and high school at [[York Mills Collegiate Institute]]. He went by his English name, Brian Kang, during that time. On October 5, 2017, he received his bachelor's degree in Business Administration from [[Dongguk University]]. He graduated from University on August 23, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201808232137542410|title=\ub370\uc774\uc2dd\uc2a4 \uc601\ucf00\uc774, \uc624\ub298(23\uc77c) \ub3d9\uad6d\ub300 \uacbd\uc601\ud559\uacfc \uc878\uc5c5 \u2018\ud559\uc0ac\ubaa8 \uc778\uc99d\uc0f7\u2019|last=Lee|first=Min-ji|date=August 23, 2018|work=Newsen|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nDuring his time in high school, Kang pursued music in a three-member band called \"3rd Degree\". They performed at various locations in Toronto and put up videos on YouTube (including some original songs composed by Kang).\n\nIn 2010, Kang and his bandmate, Don Lee, were contacted by [[JYP Entertainment]] for an audition and was accepted as trainees. Lee later left JYP to pursue medical studies. Kang went on to appear in the fourth episode of ''WIN: Who is Next?''<ref>{{Cite web|title = Preview of YG vs JYP trainees on 'WIN' revealed {{!}} allkpop.com|url = http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/09/preview-of-yg-vs-jyp-trainees-on-win-revealed|website = www.allkpop.com|access-date = 2016-01-25}}</ref> as a part of JYP's rapping team with [[Got7]]'s Mark Tuan and [[Jackson Wang]] against the combined rapping teams of [[Winner (band)|Team A]] and [[iKon (South Korean band)|Team B]], where he became known for the verse, \"[[YG Entertainment|YG]], get an attitude!\" He was also a part of JYP's vocalist team alongside his eventual [[Day6]] bandmates Junhyeok, [[Jae Park|Jae]], Sungjin and Wonpil.\n\nIn 2014, Kang was selected as a member of five-member rock band 5Live under JYP, but their debut was cancelled. The band was reformed as Day6 after the addition of drummer Dowoon in 2015.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\nKang has been credited with much of the songwriting in Day6's discography. In 2019, he composed and contributed lyrics to a track for the solo debut of [[B.A.P (South Korean band)|B.A.P]]'s Youngjae entitled \"Hope\". He has also been featured as rapper in various JYP label mates' singles, such as [[Baek A-yeon]] and [[Park Ji-min (singer, born 1997)|Park Ji-min]].{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Day6 discography}}\n\n=== Songs ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Year\n!Peak chart position\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Sales<br><small>([[Music download|DL]])</small>\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Album\n|-\n![[Gaon Digital Chart|KOR]]<br><ref>Charted songs:\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationG